ISubnet Interface

Definition

An immutable client-side representation of a subnet of a virtual network.

In this Article

public interface ISubnet : Microsoft.Azure.Management.ResourceManager.Fluent.Core.IChildResource<Microsoft.Azure.Management.Network.Fluent.INetwork>, Microsoft.Azure.Management.ResourceManager.Fluent.Core.IHasInner<Microsoft.Azure.Management.Network.Fluent.Models.SubnetInner>, Microsoft.Azure.Management.ResourceManager.Fluent.Core.IHasParent<Microsoft.Azure.Management.Network.Fluent.INetwork>

Properties

AddressPrefix

Gets the address space prefix, in CIDR notation, assigned to this subnet.
NetworkInterfaceIPConfigurationCount

Gets the number of network interface IP configurations associated with this subnet.
NetworkSecurityGroupId

Gets the resource ID of the network security group associated with this subnet, if any.
RouteTableId

Gets the resource ID of the route table associated with this subnet, if any.

Methods

GetNetworkInterfaceIPConfigurations()

Gets the network interface IP configurations that are associated with this subnet. Note that this call may result in multiple calls to Azure to fetch all the referenced interfaces each time it is invoked.
GetNetworkSecurityGroup()
GetRouteTable()
